{"word":"κίνυμαι","slug":"κίνυμαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κίνυμαι</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>= <el>κινέομαι</el>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a>,\n<p/><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a>, <i>to go, move</i>, <el>ἐς πόλεμον κίνυντο</el> (epic <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a>) they <i>were marching</i> to battle, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <el>κινυμένοιο</el> <i>as he moved</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/>"}]}